cs.IT, cs.CL, cs.LG, cs.SI, cs.DS

The paper deals with information theory concepts and their application to the analysis of written texts. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.IT (Information Theory). The paper also involves natural language processing and machine learning techniques, which suggests that it could belong to cs.CL (Computation and Language) and cs.LG (Machine Learning). The analysis of statistical dependencies among three variables could also be relevant to cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) and cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms).
